    <section id="intro">
      <span class="hero-tag">Independent Review · Updated June 2026</span>
      <h1>What Is the TD Pages &amp; Magick Link Special Offer? An Independent, Research-Based Review</h1>

      <p>The <strong>TD Pages &amp; Magick Link Special Offer</strong> is a bundled entry point into Wayne Crowe's OLSP System that pairs a $7 rotator affiliate link — the Magick Link — with a 14-day free trial of TD Pages, a landing-page builder priced at $47 per month after the trial. The central marketing claim is that every qualified click sent through your Magick Link earns $0.30, on top of standard affiliate commissions. Based on publicly available marketing pages and third-party commentary, our short take is this: the $7 entry price is genuinely low-risk and the TD Pages trial is a fair way to test a real software tool. However, the $0.30-per-click headline applies only to traffic purchased from OLSP's own in-house provider — not organic or independently sourced paid traffic — and the ongoing costs once both trials lapse can reach $70–$100 per month before any traffic spend. All earnings figures cited in promotional content are self-reported and unverified.</p>

      <div class="verdict-box">
        <p><strong>Best for:</strong> people who want a low-cost way to test a list-building workflow, are comfortable with a per-click earning model that requires buying traffic from OLSP's recommended provider, and intend to evaluate the TD Pages trial before committing to any ongoing monthly subscription.</p>
        <p><strong>Not ideal for:</strong> anyone looking for a passive or guaranteed income stream, people who want transparent and independently audited earnings data before buying, or anyone uncomfortable with recurring subscription costs that start automatically after the trial period ends.</p>
      </div>

      <h3>What Is It, and Who Is It For?</h3>
      <p>The TD Pages &amp; Magick Link Special Offer is positioned as a complete beginner's list-building system: use TD Pages to build squeeze pages that capture email opt-ins, then direct that list to your Magick Link rotator, which cycles through curated OLSP affiliate offers and earns you per-click payouts plus commissions on any upgrades. It is aimed at people with little or no email marketing experience who want a structured, pre-built entry into list-based affiliate income without building a funnel from scratch. The offer sits within the broader <a href="https://olsp.profitandprivilege.com/reviews/olsp-academy/">OLSP Academy ecosystem</a> and is designed to feed new users into the same commission system as the Mega Link training.</p>

      <h3>Author Background &amp; Review Methodology</h3>
      <div class="methodology">
        <p><strong>Who wrote this:</strong> This review was prepared by an editorial research team that evaluates online business, marketing, and digital-education products, with attention to consumer-protection norms around income claims, conditional earning structures, and subscription cost disclosure.</p>
        <p><strong>How this review was built:</strong> We did not purchase, install, or personally test the TD Pages &amp; Magick Link offer. This article is based entirely on independent desk research: the official TD Pages and Magick Link sales pages, third-party review sites, and publicly documented pricing and terms. Where a claim could not be independently verified — including all earnings figures — we say so explicitly rather than presenting it as fact.</p>
      </div>
    </section>

