      <p><strong>Target audience:</strong> Marketing copy positions the offer at complete beginners who want a done-for-you list-building setup without building a funnel from scratch. In practice, anyone evaluating it should be aware that the headline "$0.30 per click" earning requires purchasing specific traffic, not simply sharing the Magick Link freely — and that the combined monthly cost of TD Pages plus an autoresponder is a recurring financial commitment, not a one-time fee.</p>
    </section>

    <section id="design">
      <h2>Platform &amp; Build Quality</h2>
      <p>TD Pages is a web-based software-as-a-service (SaaS) landing-page builder, accessible through a browser rather than downloaded to a local machine. Based on publicly available documentation and third-party descriptions, the platform provides a drag-and-drop or template-selection interface for building squeeze pages, pop-ups, and full-screen call-to-action pages. One third-party source describes TD Pages as a white-label version of Wishloop, an established page-building platform — we could not independently verify this at the time of writing, but it is consistent with the feature set described.</p>

      <h3>Template Library and Landing Page Quality</h3>
      <p>Marketing materials for TD Pages cite "conversion rates of up to 70%," though this figure is heavily caveated on the official page itself ("depends on a number of factors — every campaign is different"). The template library is described as growing monthly, with new designs added on a rolling basis. The offer at offers.tdpages.com/magick/ positions the templates as pre-optimized specifically for OLSP-style affiliate list-building campaigns, rather than general-purpose business landing pages.</p>

      <h3>Trust Signals and Platform Risk</h3>
      <p>TD Pages offers a 30-day money-back guarantee, which provides a meaningful safety net beyond the initial 14-day trial. The Magick Link has a separate "Show Me It Works" 30-day money-back guarantee on the $7 purchase. Both guarantees are self-reported — we could not verify the refund process first-hand.</p>

      <h3>Long-Term Considerations</h3>
      <p>Both tools are tied to the OLSP ecosystem. If TD Pages changes its pricing structure, retires templates, or is discontinued, any pages you have built within the platform may become inaccessible. The Magick Link's per-click payout model depends on OLSP maintaining its current rotator and commission structure. Unlike owning your own domain and hosting independently built pages, using a SaaS tool like TD Pages means the underlying infrastructure is outside your control. This is a standard risk for all subscription page builders, not unique to TD Pages.</p>
    </section>

